how would i know if my fish had whole in the head disease some pictures of the disease would be much appreciated my fish has a small whole on the side of its gill and small dints on its head what kind of fish is it it's generally more common in oscars and other cichlids usually by the time you notice it there's pits in their head area it'll generally look discolored from the rest of the coloration on the fish here's a picture of an oscar with it http www oscarfishlover com index php option com content task view id itemid best treatment for it especially if it's an oscar do frequent water changes to keep your nitrates under ppm and vary his diet no feeder fish get a good quality pellet food and soak it in some liquid vitamins i used childrens poly vi sol or liquid centrum works too or times a week but the pellets in a bowl and just soak the pellets with the vitamin for about minutes also if it is a large fish like an oscar be sure he's in an adequate sized tank for oscar a minimum of gallons is recommended is better and have good filtration running i ran a canister and a large hang on the back filter there's still debate about what actually causes it some say high nitrates some say lack of a varied diet not enough vitamins some will say hexamita is the cause of it but from my readings hexamita is usually a secondary bacterial infection to hith disease so using an antibiotic usually metronidazole is recommended doesn't generally cure the fish of hith disease Domestic rabbit Fish farming Sewage treatment Guinea pig Shrimp farm Folic acid Diarrhea Vitamin C Common cold Marine aquarium Nutrition Acne Veganism Dairy Coronary heart disease Stomach cancer Prostate cancer Chronic fatigue syndrome Psoriasis Aquarium Beer Explosive material Hamster Vitamin D Milk Anemia Antibiotic Coeliac disease Carbon dioxide Discus (fish) Brewery Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Crohn's disease Axolotl Tofu Bong Marathon (sport) E85 Cyanocobalamin Tilapia Ulcerative colitis Paget's disease of bone Bi